YOUTUBER Thato Rampedi has scored himself a TV presenting gig on Honey’s new show, Kids Kitchen Relay. The new reality cooking show that’ll premier on 10 January will see the YouTuber co-hosting with child star Hlonela Mrwetyana and award-winning chef Zanele Van Zyl. Kids Kitchen Relay will see two teams of three go head-to-head in a relay cooking competition. Each team is given a theme and the members take turns to prepare one dish over three rounds. Thato, who has over 118 000 subscribers and was part of YouTube Black Voices Class of 2021, said he is excited about the show. “I genuinely cannot wait for the show to air! Being on set was such an experience and I cannot wait for the people to see what we did! Definitely 10 out of 10,” he said. ALSO READ : MEETING THE KING WITH LWAZI! He has also bagged multiple lucrative brand deals ranging from Canon, Lenovo and Sennheiser. Hlonela, who is currently a Preteen Universe Finalist for 2022, said: “It has been such a rewarding experience. I feel confident and I am very appreciative because I got to work with some amazing people that made the experience fun.” Chef Zanele, who is also an author, said she has wanted to be part of a cooking show for a long time. “I have always wanted to be on a cooking show. The thought of me being a judge on a kids cooking show never crossed my mind.” Honey’s head of content Zinzi Velelo said viewers will enjoy the show. “It’s such a dynamic show because these aren’t just kids who are pretending to cook. They’re invested in the competition. A lot of them actually want to be chefs and it shows. Viewers are in for a treat,” she said. Catch the Kids Kitchen Relay premiere on Monday, 10 January at 4.30pm on Honey DStv channel 173.